        </td>
        <td style="height:21px;">
          <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_"><text styleclass="Heading3_atocs_" translate="true">Application Notes</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">Cross-Over Jerk is Zero. Thus it is good motion-law where there is backlash. It is especially useful for those high-speed mechanisms where a moderate amount of backlash cannot be avoided.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Motion-Law-Coefficients" styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">Motion Coefficients</link></para>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" translate="true">Cv = 1.667</text></para>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" translate="true">Ca = 5.926</text></para>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" translate="true">Cj = 80, -26.667</text></para>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" translate="true">Cj at </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Cross-Over" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" translate="true">Crossover</link><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" translate="true"> = 0.0</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
